column2: Aquatic plants less present as two weeks earlier.
Small white caps- cloudy with sun.
No wind- cloudy- sparse rain drops.

Sunny and light breeze.  Lake turns a bit harder to see into after it has rained.  All the readings were taken at about 20' of depth- close to the same location on the lake.  Lake activity with the exception of two weekends is quite minimal.  We are fortunate! / Sunny and light breeze.
Sprinkles - no wind - fairly clear sky.
Robert Hill 10'- Bev Hill 13.5'.  11.75' entered as average.
